# Planning And Execution

- Translate requests into concrete outcomes before implementing.
- Break work into small, verifiable steps and complete end-to-end.
- Surface blockers early with proposed defaults or options.
- Keep edits focused; do not refactor unrelated areas unless requested.
- If there are multiple valid approaches, pick the simplest one and explain why.
- Record assumptions and TODO placeholders when project-specific values are missing.
